<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,618,1687]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1554,1579]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[669,765,1554,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tlaloc">
<emphasis box="[669,765,1554,1579]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">A. tlaloc</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the clypeus with the apical margin rounded; the mandible distinctly narrow with the two lower teeth distinct and longer than the others; the eye large; and the mesopleuron without longitudinal striae, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[722,819,1626,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tlaloc">
<emphasis box="[722,819,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">A. tlaloc</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the mandible wide, curved, and step-shaped with five distal teeth; the eye small; and the mesopleuron with longitudinal striae.
</paragraph>
